The psychology of overselling: why spend more money?
Buyers are willing to spend more, to overestimate the goods.
Researchers neurologists and economists at the University of New York have been able to discover the neuro-economic bases of this known and seemingly irrational behavior.
According to their study published on Science magazine, men do not want to stay back in a competition such as eBay auction, so they are also available to pay a higher price.
The research has tried to trace the nervous scheme of this "party" at the level of the nervous system through experimental auctions.
A group of volunteers played the lottery, the other group of players participated in an auction while using the functional magnetic resonance method (fMRI) examined the active areas of the brain of the people involved in the experiment.
In both games participants could win money, but in the game of auction, in which the essential element is to bid more than the other, the body stretched under the brain cortex becomes intensively functioning when you lose the game.
This brain area, in addition to other functions, plays a role in the "self-gratification" mechanism of the nervous system.
Therefore, according to researchers, the rise in price is explained by scanning the true reaction of the stretched body.
In order to support their theory, the economists of the research group conducted a financial investigation.
In this investigation, three groups have appealed against a partner under different conditions.
The control group reported the actual value of the product concerned and made them their point.
To another group, they have also promised that in the event of winnings they will receive another $15 prize.
The third group would have received $15 before the auction, but the members of the group would have lost the money if the auction was lost.
The difference between the two groups consisted in the fact that for one of them the winning was highlighted, while for the other the loss.
Checking the hypothesis of the neurologists the members of the group who played "against loss" were willing to make higher points of the control group or "winning".
"These results are not deductible from any of the previously existing economic theories.
In fact, they have so far explained the phenomena that are susceptible to auctions with the joy of winning and with the avoidance of risk.
Only the methods of creating the neurological image helped resolve the contradiction between the two theories, so that we came to a third explanation" - said Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics at the University of New York.
Hepatitis: when to talk to your doctor?
Almost half a billion people in the world are suffering from chronic hepatitis B or C, but chronic liver diseases are mentioned in Hungary among the first causes of death.
In Hungary, the number of hepatitis patients increases to one hundred thousand, of which only 7,000 are treated: the reason is that many patients do not know how to be infected.
The definition of hepatitis is the collective name of infectious liver diseases caused by various viruses.
There are many similarities between symptoms, typical are hepatitis and ittery, but their pathogens and the diseases caused differ from one another.
Hepatitis viruses are spread in two main forms depending on the pathogen agent: hepatitis A and E through the food channel (e.g. water and infected foods), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and organic fluids (sperm, vaginal loss, salt).
For those travelling it is useful to immunize against virus A and B, against C no vaccine exists.
Symptoms of hepatitis A appear two to three weeks after consumption of infected foods, accompanied by general nausea, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After they form yellow spots on the skin and on the white of the eyes, the faeces become clear and the dark urine, the healing takes place within two to three weeks.
One million people die every year worldwide for hepatitis B, the most serious variant of the disease, causing liver and liver cirrhosis.
The main reason, according to estimates, is that only one person in ten receives pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: if it is not treated it can cause liver cirrhosis and tumours.
Most infected people do not know that they have contracted the disease because pathogens subdominate the liver cells, in many cases the first symptoms appear after 20-30 years.
Therefore, it is very important to prevent and carry out regular medical tests.
This disease is much more frequent than the average in three groups: those who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug addicts and tattoos.
In the world today, the number of people infected with chronic hepatitis C virus is 200 million.
Because also a routine laboratory test reveals the disease is worth addressing your family doctor when you notice any symptoms of unknown origin.
Recognized in time the disease is curable, the virus can be eliminated from the body, so it stops the infective power and can prevent the formation of tumors.
On September 30, it is the world day of the hepatitis, organized for the first time in 2004 around the world by associations of patients.
The aim is to draw attention to the chronic viral hepatitis, the causes of its development and early recognition of the disease.
Who believes in God feels less pain?
According to a recent survey, religious faith works as a kind of analgesic that has made the death of Catholic martyrs more bearable.
Scientists at the University of Oxford conducted an interesting experiment, examining how faith in God affects the feeling of pain, reported the British Telegraph.
In the context of a rather bizarre investigation, an electroshock was performed to 12 Catholic believers and to similar atheists, while all who observed a painting depicting the Virgin Mary.
Based on the results, the Catholic believers were able to reject much of the pain.
Thanks to the exploratory technique of the human brain, it was discovered that Catholics were able to activate the part of the brain responsible for controlling the pain.
The test is the first of a series of research in which, in addition to academics, scientists, philosophers and theologians of the University also take part.
The test took place exactly like this: an instrument that emits discharges and passes the electroshock was connected to the left hand of the subject of the experiment.
The researchers asked the participants to focus on two paintings, the Virgin Mary painted in the 17th century by Sassoferrato and the Lady with the ring of Leonardo da Vinci painted in the 15th century.
The authors of the exam hoped that the image of the Virgin Mary originated a sort of religious state among the believers, while Leonardo's picture was chosen because it was not too different from the other and they considered it to be a calming effect.
The subjects of the experiment spent half an hour in front of the MRI scanner and in this time zone they received 20 electroshocks in four consecutive series, while observing either the painting on a religious theme or the other.
The Catholics reported that the vision of the Virgin Mary made them feel "sure", as if "someone took care" of them and "they were calm and were overcome by peace".
Looking at the image on the religious theme, they accounted for 12% less pain than when they had before themselves the work of Leonardo.
The psychologist Miguel Farias, who took part in the test himself, believes that such a result can be achieved with any image of the strong effect even for atheists, but we need to find the right image.
"We need to look for an image to which they nurture very positive feelings, such as a mother or a father," said the psychologist.
The Anglican bishop Tom Wright was pleased with the result of the search.
"The practice of faith should change, and in many cases it can change our personality." - Wright added.
After the excellent results, only the question remains if the believers are presented with the painting of a lady of Leonardo or another painter of such a caliber, what effect could it have on the control of the pain?
Would the vision of a quality virgin Mary bring better results?
