The export sales prices of the industry reported in July 2008 were higher than 1.1%, whereas the previous year they decreased by 3.9%.
As a result of the change in domestic prices and exports, industrial production costs were higher than 0.7% compared to the previous month and 3.2% compared to one year ago.
The prices of domestic industrial sales reported in the previous month only increased by 0.1%.
National sales prices in the manufacturing sector have also risen to a minimum of 0.1% compared to July.
The higher prices in August 2008 occurred in the field of leather and footwear processing (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and the production of shoes with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price of plastic and chemical raw materials has led to a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the chemicals and products sector.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of instruments and electrical machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum extent in the wood processing (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, editorial and typographical activities have not changed.
In other sectors of the processing industry there was an increase in prices between 0.2% and 0.9%.
