A decrease in prices occurred in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.3%).
In other sectors of the processing industry, the rate of price increase varies from 0.6% to 9.1%.
Overall, in the manufacturing industry over the past year, prices rose by 10.2%.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded 18.7% of those in last year.
In national sales among target groups in the sectors, the highest monthly price increase occurred in August in the sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In sectors producing consumer goods prices have risen by 0.3%, in the energy and subsequent use sectors prices have not changed compared to those of the previous month.
