We also need to review existing control systems, in the light of this scientific opinion, in order to ensure that they are fully effective and step-by-step with new technology."
Brussels had asked the independent Scientific Committee to examine the problem, given the large use of portable musical instruments and the increase in the number of young people exposed to noise from them.
"Scientists - concluded by Executive Ue - confirm that there is a cause for concern and the European Commission will now examine with the Member States and stakeholders what measures could be taken to better protect children and adolescents from exposure to noise from portable musical devices and similar equipment."
